metadata.description: Based on true events. Everything you need to know is in the music.

lyrics.text:
Mobbin round with the hoodie on
I’m blacked up, strapped up, ready for it if they bring it him
16 with a healthy hesitation around shape shifters
Grew three inches over the summer, rep a little bigger 
Cuz he can dunk now, first pick in the runs now 
Sun up to sundown, get respect when I come round 
But that ain’t good enough, I’m looking for the level up 
That feel good right now, any work is for chippers
Need that tribute right now 

Now follow me down this road that I’m traveling 
Ground that I’m planted in, look around me it’s the dirtiest, I
Supposed to be the rose that split the shit and gave you hope, I 
Born a miracle, at least my momma told me so 

It’s a ego show, I’m driven by the glow 
Who get fly now, you gon hear me coming down the road 
I got that Dre sound 
Built me a unit I could commune with
A community, Niggas is hungry, I mean that literally

I know now, it's only mine, if it meant for me  
But back then, we would take anything, we was willing 
To act up, you know when you younger you do that dumb shit cuz reality, ain’t happen to us yet, you dream of fantasy, off Hennessy 
We would hang out few blocks from Genesee 
Seattle streets, best kept secret, I had to leak it
The amenities, is good times, some gray skies
But on a bad day, you’re best friend might end their life 
Or maybe jealousy, ain’t too many of us given the structures for real wins 
Some lack family, some mistaking boys for real men
Some lack god, consider luck if yours is built in
I get high… spirits talk to me like we real friends 

Why can’t I, let go of time, that’s revealing 
Dated a smart woman but she ain’t won’t to have my children 
My traumas not far enough behind me and I can pass it
She said she ain’t want no one ever calling her son bastid

Abuse the ability end parties early, that’s a tactic
Survival matters in the midst of madness, where your mask at?
Learned it, we was sitting in the rafters, watching ballers 
Seen prodigies turn to alcoholics 

Was babies with the pagers and two ways
Big homie said he’d watch over me, he in the 12th grade
Snuck to Latoya house to get some on them half days 
Lost my focus starin around that ass, I moved sideways 
My first real lessons and real losses
Missteps dealing with decisions the heart causes 
A chasm, a spasm, sent here to test um, was listening to amateurs that’s how you get your chest hurt. 

And leave damages, I’m sitting round reflecting on my staminas, moves I used to get advantages 
The shoes I fill to put the steps in 
The mops that I used to clean the messes up
